A clean way to remove wiggle-room without sounding punitive is to spell out objective, observable exit criteria for every deliverable and explicitly shut down the usual loopholes. Something like:

“Each assigned Jira ticket must be:  
• moved to ‘Done’ status in Jira by 5 p.m. local time each Friday, with all subtasks completed and the resolution field set to ‘Fixed’;  
• accompanied by a merge request that has passed all automated CI checks and has been approved by at least one peer reviewer (not the employee themselves) before the same 5 p.m. deadline;  
• free of any P1/P2 defects reported in the 48-hour post-merge monitoring window;  
• documented with a concise, one-paragraph summary of changes and test evidence, posted in the ticket before the deadline.”

If a ticket is blocked, the employee must note the blocker in Jira and notify you in writing by Thursday 5 p.m.; otherwise, the “Done” criteria remain unchanged.

Would you like me to expand that into a fuller PIP section, or tweak any of the checkpoints?
